1
00:00:00,050 --> 00:00:01,217
(All characters, organizations,
and events in this drama are fictitious.)

2
00:00:01,217 --> 00:00:02,617
(Filming complied with guidelines
for children, youth, and animals.)

3
00:00:04,217 --> 00:00:05,417
What's with Seo Seung Ri?

4
00:00:06,217 --> 00:00:09,050
She seems full of energy.
Something feels different.

5
00:00:11,150 --> 00:00:12,217
Wait.

6
00:00:12,317 --> 00:00:15,150
Let's see the business plan materials.

7
00:00:23,517 --> 00:00:24,250
(Application for Admission
to the MBA Program)

8
00:00:24,250 --> 00:00:25,250
What's this?

9
00:00:30,017 --> 00:00:31,617
Why are you looking through my laptop?

10
00:00:34,517 --> 00:00:35,517
So this was it?

11
00:00:36,450 --> 00:00:39,250
The reason you still haven't let go
of your hope for Gyeol...

12
00:00:40,017 --> 00:00:41,617
Is it because you're planning
to follow him to the U.S.?

13
00:00:42,417 --> 00:00:43,750
That's not the only reason.

14
00:00:44,450 --> 00:00:47,950
I'd been thinking about an MBA
even before I joined Kangsu Construction.

15
00:00:48,817 --> 00:00:51,517
Before it's too late, I want to continue
the studies I've always wanted to pursue.

16
00:00:51,817 --> 00:00:52,817
Seo Seung Ri.

17
00:00:53,017 --> 00:00:54,450
Don't worry.

18
00:00:54,450 --> 00:00:57,717
I'll do my best for Team One
until the competition is over.

19
00:00:57,717 --> 00:01:01,617
Do you think
that's what I'm worried about?

20
00:01:03,517 --> 00:01:05,650
How far are you willing to take this?

21
00:01:06,417 --> 00:01:08,117
He doesn't even have feelings for you,

22
00:01:08,117 --> 00:01:09,417
so what's the point of following him?

23
00:01:09,617 --> 00:01:11,450
Keep your voice down. We're at work.

24
00:01:12,417 --> 00:01:13,950
As for the life I've chosen for myself,

25
00:01:14,417 --> 00:01:17,117
I don't think
you should be interfering in it like this.

26
00:01:22,650 --> 00:01:24,817
I'm sorry.
I guess the meeting isn't over yet.

27
00:01:25,017 --> 00:01:26,517
The other employees are outside, so...

28
00:01:34,650 --> 00:01:38,450
Sorry, we've been using
the conference room all day.

29
00:01:39,017 --> 00:01:40,617
We'll probably be done in about an hour.

30
00:01:41,317 --> 00:01:43,650
Not at all. If you still need it,
we'll hold our meeting in the office.

31
00:01:46,417 --> 00:01:49,717
By the way,
is there something going on with Chief Ko?

32
00:01:50,717 --> 00:01:52,717
No. Nothing at all.

33
00:01:53,417 --> 00:01:55,517
- Then...
- Gyeol.

34
00:01:57,750 --> 00:01:59,017
I'm sorry about the other day.

35
00:02:02,850 --> 00:02:07,250
I got too emotional
in front of Ms. Cho Eun Ae's house.

36
00:02:07,550 --> 00:02:08,617
I apologize.

37
00:02:09,317 --> 00:02:10,317
No.

38
00:02:11,217 --> 00:02:13,817
You were just taking Ms. Cho Eun Ae home.

39
00:02:14,350 --> 00:02:16,917
I misunderstood.
I'm the one who should apologize.

40
00:02:18,117 --> 00:02:19,317
It's okay. Forget about it.

41
00:02:19,950 --> 00:02:22,717
And about pushing you
to review the Joy report...

42
00:02:23,317 --> 00:02:25,417
I was the one being emotional back then.
I'm sorry.

43
00:02:26,617 --> 00:02:27,650
It wasn't a misunderstanding.

44
00:02:28,517 --> 00:02:31,317
I had already figured out that you two
were living in the same house.

45
00:02:33,017 --> 00:02:35,517
I went there on purpose because I wanted
to see it with my own eyes.

46
00:02:36,750 --> 00:02:40,517
And I was too emotional
about the Joy report too.

47
00:02:40,850 --> 00:02:42,517
It wasn't professional of me.

48
00:02:43,850 --> 00:02:45,517
Okay. Anyway...

49
00:02:46,317 --> 00:02:47,750
Thanks for being honest with me.

50
00:02:49,217 --> 00:02:52,117
Gyeol, I...

51
00:02:57,117 --> 00:02:58,217
Never mind.

52
00:02:59,050 --> 00:03:01,850
Let's focus on competing
in the remaining rounds.

53
00:03:03,050 --> 00:03:04,617
Okay. Let's do that.

54
00:03:12,250 --> 00:03:13,850
It's okay. Don't cry.

55
00:03:15,117 --> 00:03:17,117
I miss Mom.

56
00:03:17,117 --> 00:03:20,017
Mom.

57
00:03:20,150 --> 00:03:23,417
- I miss Mom.
- Mom will come back soon.

58
00:03:23,617 --> 00:03:24,617
Bit Na.

59
00:03:25,217 --> 00:03:26,717
Dad!

60
00:03:31,417 --> 00:03:33,250
Why won't the door to our house open?

61
00:03:33,750 --> 00:03:35,017
Where's Mom?

62
00:03:35,850 --> 00:03:38,817
Why isn't she answering my calls
or coming home?

63
00:03:40,217 --> 00:03:42,750
I'm sorry, Bit Na. I'm so sorry.

64
00:03:43,017 --> 00:03:45,517
Tell Mom to come home quickly.

65
00:03:45,917 --> 00:03:48,650
Tell her I'm waiting.

66
00:03:49,050 --> 00:03:50,417
Okay.

67
00:03:51,550 --> 00:03:53,517
I will tell her. I'll tell her right away.

68
00:03:53,517 --> 00:03:56,017
- Mom.
- I'm sorry. You must've been scared.

69
00:03:56,750 --> 00:03:59,617
Mom.

70
00:04:00,950 --> 00:04:02,150
Don't cry.

71
00:04:02,150 --> 00:04:04,517
- What do we do?
- It's okay. Don't cry.

72
00:04:04,517 --> 00:04:07,317
- My poor baby.
- Dad will tell her right away. I'm sorry.

73
00:04:08,384 --> 00:04:10,417
Did you break up with Mom?

74
00:04:11,484 --> 00:04:15,184
Why?
Because she couldn't get the apples back?

75
00:04:16,317 --> 00:04:18,884
No, that's not it.

76
00:04:19,917 --> 00:04:21,517
Mom says she's suffering...

77
00:04:21,984 --> 00:04:24,917
because all the apples in our house
disappeared because of her.

78
00:04:25,884 --> 00:04:27,884
So she says she can't live with us
right now.

79
00:04:28,717 --> 00:04:31,784
But Mom didn't abandon you, Bit Na.

80
00:04:31,984 --> 00:04:34,384
She asked me to take care of you
and left for a while.

81
00:04:34,917 --> 00:04:37,284
Then, when is Mom coming back?

82
00:04:38,184 --> 00:04:39,784
I don't know.

83
00:04:40,484 --> 00:04:43,584
I think she'll come back...

84
00:04:43,984 --> 00:04:45,217
after she's overcome all her pain.

85
00:04:46,017 --> 00:04:49,184
But Mom loves you very much,

86
00:04:49,984 --> 00:04:51,484
so it won't take too long.

87
00:04:51,817 --> 00:04:55,584
Then, when she comes back,
are we all going to live together again?

88
00:04:57,584 --> 00:05:01,084
No. Probably not.

89
00:05:02,117 --> 00:05:05,317
But whenever you miss Mom,
you can see her.

90
00:05:05,717 --> 00:05:09,484
And whenever Mom misses you,
she promised she'll come see you too.

91
00:05:10,017 --> 00:05:13,317
No!
I don't want to see Mom only sometimes.

92
00:05:13,750 --> 00:05:16,084
We should live together every day.

93
00:05:16,817 --> 00:05:19,117
Mom.

94
00:05:23,117 --> 00:05:25,150
I'm sorry, Bit Na.

95
00:05:28,417 --> 00:05:32,217
What? Bit Na went to their old house
looking for her mom?

96
00:05:32,717 --> 00:05:33,717
Yeah.

97
00:05:34,317 --> 00:05:35,950
I can't do this anymore, honey.

98
00:05:35,950 --> 00:05:38,217
We need to go see Ji Seon right away.

99
00:05:38,450 --> 00:05:41,217
Her phone's turned off. So how?

100
00:05:42,017 --> 00:05:45,517
Then I'll go to her office tomorrow.

101
00:05:47,817 --> 00:05:48,817
No.

102
00:05:49,917 --> 00:05:52,617
Come with me
to her parents' house right now.

103
00:05:53,017 --> 00:05:55,317
You know where her parents live, right?

104
00:05:56,250 --> 00:05:57,517
Go get changed right now.

105
00:05:57,517 --> 00:05:59,617
Honey, please calm down.

106
00:05:59,917 --> 00:06:03,317
What are you going to accomplish
by going there right now?

107
00:06:03,317 --> 00:06:07,350
There's still a cooling-off period.
We can still fix this.

108
00:06:10,817 --> 00:06:12,417
That long meeting must've worn you out.

109
00:06:12,750 --> 00:06:13,917
I wasn't the only one.

110
00:06:14,150 --> 00:06:15,650
Tomorrow's going to be just as intense,

111
00:06:15,650 --> 00:06:17,517
so skip your workout tonight
and get some sleep.

112
00:06:18,217 --> 00:06:20,017
I can take care of myself.

113
00:06:20,217 --> 00:06:21,517
You always treat me like a child.

114
00:06:26,817 --> 00:06:28,517
Then why did you tell Bit Na's mom...

115
00:06:28,517 --> 00:06:31,750
she could still be a mom
even after the divorce? Why?

116
00:06:32,650 --> 00:06:33,850
Then what do you want me to do?

117
00:06:34,117 --> 00:06:36,217
Just sit back
and watch Bit Na suffer like that?

118
00:06:37,417 --> 00:06:38,517
What's going on?

119
00:06:38,617 --> 00:06:41,650
You're right. I was wrong.

120
00:06:42,417 --> 00:06:45,850
Back then, I was disappointed in everyone
and exhausted.

121
00:06:46,517 --> 00:06:48,817
I didn't want Ji Seon to end up like me.

122
00:06:49,417 --> 00:06:50,517
But no.

123
00:06:51,217 --> 00:06:52,517
This can't go on.

124
00:06:52,517 --> 00:06:54,717
We have to undo this somehow.

125
00:06:54,717 --> 00:06:57,217
And you think you can undo everything now?

126
00:06:57,717 --> 00:06:59,817
They made this decision
after a lot of thought.

127
00:06:59,917 --> 00:07:01,017
How would you know?

128
00:07:01,317 --> 00:07:05,050
Do you even know what it feels like
to be abandoned by your mom?

129
00:07:05,517 --> 00:07:06,517
Honey.

130
00:07:06,717 --> 00:07:09,450
You don't know.
You've never lived through it.

131
00:07:09,917 --> 00:07:11,950
Being abandoned by your mom
without even knowing why...

132
00:07:12,117 --> 00:07:14,750
You think, "She'll come today."
"She'll be here when I wake up."

133
00:07:14,750 --> 00:07:16,650
"She'll come."
"She'll definitely come get me."

134
00:07:17,650 --> 00:07:20,217
Then one month becomes two.

135
00:07:20,417 --> 00:07:21,850
One year becomes two.

136
00:07:23,317 --> 00:07:25,117
And eventually,
you realize you've been abandoned.

137
00:07:25,550 --> 00:07:28,617
You spend the rest of your life feeling
like your very existence was denied.

138
00:07:28,950 --> 00:07:31,717
You have no idea how terrifying
and heartbreaking that is...

139
00:07:32,150 --> 00:07:34,417
because you've never lived through it!

140
00:07:35,117 --> 00:07:37,217
Honey, please.

141
00:07:38,350 --> 00:07:41,250
One person carrying that wound is enough.

142
00:07:41,917 --> 00:07:45,050
No matter what it takes,
I'm bringing Ji Seon back.

143
00:07:57,217 --> 00:07:59,317
Team Manager Ko, when did you get here?

144
00:07:59,517 --> 00:08:00,750
Just now.

145
00:08:02,117 --> 00:08:03,950
Don't worry too much.
Go upstairs and get some rest.

146
00:08:05,750 --> 00:08:06,750
Okay.

147
00:08:16,550 --> 00:08:17,550
I'm sorry.

148
00:08:18,550 --> 00:08:20,350
I'm sorry. Bit Na fell asleep.

149
00:08:20,650 --> 00:08:21,850
I'll take her out right away.

150
00:08:21,850 --> 00:08:23,117
No, it's fine.

151
00:08:24,617 --> 00:08:28,017
Actually, I just remembered
something came up at my parents' house.

152
00:08:28,017 --> 00:08:29,350
I'm going to sleep there tonight.

153
00:08:29,417 --> 00:08:31,117
No, don't do that because of us.

154
00:08:31,717 --> 00:08:32,950
I'll wake her and take her out.

155
00:08:33,217 --> 00:08:35,217
No. Let Bit Na sleep.

156
00:08:35,650 --> 00:08:38,117
I want to see my grandpa too,
so I'll go home.

157
00:08:38,117 --> 00:08:39,117
Get some rest.

158
00:08:39,317 --> 00:08:40,317
But...

159
00:09:07,017 --> 00:09:08,550
Mom, are you okay?

160
00:09:10,250 --> 00:09:11,517
How did you know I'd be here?

161
00:09:12,717 --> 00:09:16,217
I just had a feeling.

162
00:09:18,750 --> 00:09:20,017
I had no idea...

163
00:09:20,817 --> 00:09:24,017
you were carrying such a deep wound.

164
00:09:25,017 --> 00:09:26,550
You should've told us sooner.

165
00:09:29,450 --> 00:09:30,750
I didn't want...

166
00:09:33,217 --> 00:09:36,117
to pass my pain...

167
00:09:37,117 --> 00:09:38,617
and my darkness on to you.

168
00:09:41,417 --> 00:09:43,317
So I kept my mouth shut my whole life.

169
00:09:44,517 --> 00:09:45,517
I hoped...

170
00:09:46,717 --> 00:09:48,317
you'd never find out.

171
00:09:52,317 --> 00:09:53,317
The powder compact...

172
00:09:54,617 --> 00:09:58,017
and necklace you kept hidden
in the wardrobe...

173
00:09:58,817 --> 00:10:02,517
Did they belong to your mom?
To my grandma?

174
00:10:06,617 --> 00:10:08,850
I kept meaning to throw them away.

175
00:10:09,117 --> 00:10:10,650
But I never could.

176
00:10:13,117 --> 00:10:14,450
Pathetic, isn't it?

177
00:10:16,317 --> 00:10:18,950
Getting attached
to a broken compact and an old necklace.

178
00:10:25,817 --> 00:10:28,117
The day I left you here,

179
00:10:31,150 --> 00:10:33,017
I saw someone who looked like my mom...

180
00:10:34,017 --> 00:10:35,750
and followed her without thinking.

181
00:10:39,117 --> 00:10:41,950
I completely forgot
my own child was waiting for me here.

182
00:10:44,550 --> 00:10:45,650
So that's what happened.

183
00:10:48,917 --> 00:10:52,617
You must've suffered so much, Mom.

184
00:10:56,017 --> 00:10:57,017
Mom.

185
00:10:57,917 --> 00:11:00,717
Don't you want to find Grandma?

186
00:11:01,150 --> 00:11:02,150
What?

187
00:11:02,150 --> 00:11:05,617
Maybe she had her reasons.
Just like you did that day.

188
00:11:06,717 --> 00:11:10,550
Maybe she's still looking for you
somewhere.

189
00:11:11,217 --> 00:11:12,217
No.

190
00:11:14,117 --> 00:11:15,717
She really abandoned me.

191
00:11:17,550 --> 00:11:19,117
She threw away her own child...

192
00:11:21,017 --> 00:11:22,950
to pursue her own happiness.

193
00:11:23,250 --> 00:11:24,517
Mom.

194
00:11:24,517 --> 00:11:26,250
I don't have a mom.

195
00:11:27,850 --> 00:11:29,417
So don't ever...

196
00:11:30,550 --> 00:11:32,350
bring up your maternal grandma again.

197
00:11:34,450 --> 00:11:35,450
That woman...

198
00:11:37,950 --> 00:11:39,917
has been dead in my heart for a long time.

199
00:11:54,917 --> 00:11:57,217
Why didn't you tell us you were coming?

200
00:11:57,850 --> 00:11:59,450
You must be busy preparing
for the competition.

201
00:11:59,950 --> 00:12:01,817
I suddenly wanted to see you,
Grandma, Grandpa.

202
00:12:02,017 --> 00:12:03,117
I'm glad you came, Gyeol.

203
00:12:03,617 --> 00:12:07,117
I've been sad all this time
because we missed each other last time.

204
00:12:07,917 --> 00:12:10,217
By the way,
knowing you're living in that house...

205
00:12:10,650 --> 00:12:12,750
gives me such peace of mind.

206
00:12:13,117 --> 00:12:17,117
Your grandma can't stop
praising that family.

207
00:12:17,350 --> 00:12:19,650
They really are warm, wonderful people.

208
00:12:20,550 --> 00:12:23,650
And you're still getting along well
with that young lady?

209
00:12:24,150 --> 00:12:26,317
Of course. We're working hard together.

210
00:12:28,017 --> 00:12:30,117
Is work all you're doing?

211
00:12:30,850 --> 00:12:31,850
Sorry?

212
00:12:32,017 --> 00:12:33,450
What's that supposed to mean, Yeong Hwa?

213
00:12:33,817 --> 00:12:35,317
Sounds like you're asking...

214
00:12:35,750 --> 00:12:38,217
whether they're more than just co-workers.

215
00:12:38,517 --> 00:12:39,817
Did it sound that way?

216
00:12:40,517 --> 00:12:42,650
I was only teasing.

217
00:12:43,917 --> 00:12:46,850
I'd like to see her too.

218
00:12:47,317 --> 00:12:48,517
That Joy developer.

219
00:12:49,117 --> 00:12:50,317
Tell her to come visit sometime.

220
00:12:50,317 --> 00:12:51,617
Visit here?

221
00:12:52,017 --> 00:12:53,517
I'll ask her.

222
00:12:53,817 --> 00:12:54,817
And...

223
00:12:55,517 --> 00:12:57,650
I'd like to take your grandma on a date.

224
00:12:58,050 --> 00:12:59,617
Can you recommend somewhere?

225
00:13:01,150 --> 00:13:02,750
Don't even start.

226
00:13:03,317 --> 00:13:06,017
The last time you took me flower viewing,

227
00:13:06,417 --> 00:13:08,117
I nearly lost my mind.

228
00:13:09,217 --> 00:13:10,650
That won't happen again.

229
00:13:11,317 --> 00:13:13,717
Can't you see how energetic I am now?

230
00:13:14,517 --> 00:13:17,117
Then I'll plan a simple day trip
so you won't overdo it.

231
00:13:17,117 --> 00:13:18,217
How about this weekend?

232
00:13:18,717 --> 00:13:20,050
Sounds good to me.

233
00:13:20,917 --> 00:13:23,150
Are you really okay?

234
00:13:33,917 --> 00:13:34,917
Good grief.

235
00:13:36,050 --> 00:13:37,717
For a second there,
I thought you were a monster.

236
00:13:37,717 --> 00:13:39,950
You know, that green-faced one.

237
00:13:39,950 --> 00:13:41,850
What's it called? Shr... Something.

238
00:13:41,850 --> 00:13:45,017
I've been wearing that visor all day,
and it's giving me a headache.

239
00:13:45,317 --> 00:13:47,617
So I found another way
to hide my expression.

240
00:13:48,350 --> 00:13:50,717
But seriously, I told Gyeol...

241
00:13:50,717 --> 00:13:52,750
to invite his grandparents over.

242
00:13:52,750 --> 00:13:53,917
Why did he come here instead?

243
00:13:54,317 --> 00:13:56,017
Does he enjoy rubbing salt
in the wound or what?

244
00:13:56,017 --> 00:13:59,017
Exactly.
We need those two out of the house.

245
00:13:59,250 --> 00:14:00,717
I put in all that effort
to come up with a plan.

246
00:14:02,217 --> 00:14:04,450
Good grief! Yong Man!

247
00:14:04,750 --> 00:14:06,117
How long have you been standing there?

248
00:14:06,117 --> 00:14:09,217
A while. Since that green monster
came out of the room.

249
00:14:09,217 --> 00:14:10,217
Mister!

250
00:14:10,817 --> 00:14:14,550
You asked me to check the water pressure
in the bathroom.

251
00:14:15,217 --> 00:14:16,217
I'm done.

252
00:14:16,217 --> 00:14:18,117
If you're done, then go back to the annex.

253
00:14:18,117 --> 00:14:19,817
You're usually asleep by this hour.

254
00:14:21,517 --> 00:14:22,717
What could it be?

255
00:14:23,350 --> 00:14:26,617
Why are you two so desperate...

256
00:14:26,617 --> 00:14:28,917
for the Chairman and Madam
to leave the house?

257
00:14:30,550 --> 00:14:32,617
That guy, seriously...

258
00:14:34,917 --> 00:14:37,617
As they say, "Chairs have ears."

259
00:14:38,850 --> 00:14:42,117
Crystal, I've been thinking this
for a long time.

260
00:14:42,117 --> 00:14:44,950
Maybe from now on, you should stop...

261
00:14:45,217 --> 00:14:47,117
using proverbs and idioms altogether.

262
00:14:47,617 --> 00:14:49,817
Why? Did I get it wrong again?

263
00:14:50,317 --> 00:14:53,817
"Chairs have ears." It's correct.

264
00:14:57,350 --> 00:14:58,917
Nothing to be surprised about.

265
00:14:59,350 --> 00:15:01,450
You know how serious I am about skincare.

266
00:15:02,950 --> 00:15:04,417
But Gyeol, what happened?

267
00:15:04,417 --> 00:15:06,250
I told you to invite your grandparents...

268
00:15:06,250 --> 00:15:09,117
to the place you're living,
so how did you end up coming here?

269
00:15:09,850 --> 00:15:11,917
I haven't had a chance
to ask my landlord yet.

270
00:15:12,317 --> 00:15:15,517
And this weekend, I'm planning
to take Grandpa and Grandma somewhere.

271
00:15:16,250 --> 00:15:18,217
Really? That's great.

272
00:15:18,217 --> 00:15:19,917
That's how you should show
your filial devotion.

273
00:15:19,917 --> 00:15:21,417
Good job. Nice.

274
00:15:21,550 --> 00:15:23,317
I'll head upstairs now.

275
00:15:23,317 --> 00:15:24,717
I'm staying the night here.

276
00:15:24,717 --> 00:15:27,717
Sure. Get some good rest. Bonne nuit.

277
00:15:29,017 --> 00:15:30,817
- Okay.
- Right.

278
00:15:39,217 --> 00:15:40,850
Did she get home okay?

279
00:15:45,417 --> 00:15:46,417
Ko Gyeol.

280
00:15:47,450 --> 00:15:49,517
You rejected her confession yourself,

281
00:15:49,517 --> 00:15:50,817
and now you're doing this?

282
00:15:53,517 --> 00:15:56,117
Still, I think I can at least ask...

283
00:15:56,617 --> 00:15:57,917
how her mother is doing.

284
00:16:02,317 --> 00:16:04,817
Hello, Eun Ae. Are you home?

285
00:16:05,350 --> 00:16:07,117
Yes, I got home a little while ago.

286
00:16:08,350 --> 00:16:10,750
Did you go home
because of my brother and Bit Na?

287
00:16:11,517 --> 00:16:14,617
No.
I was planning to see my grandpa anyway.

288
00:16:15,217 --> 00:16:16,517
How is your mother doing?

289
00:16:17,417 --> 00:16:19,250
She's calmed down a lot.

290
00:16:21,617 --> 00:16:22,850
You must've been shocked today.

291
00:16:24,217 --> 00:16:26,217
More worried than shocked.

292
00:16:26,950 --> 00:16:29,650
I worry about your mother,
Bit Na, your brother...

293
00:16:30,217 --> 00:16:31,317
and you too, Ms. Cho Eun Ae.

294
00:16:31,317 --> 00:16:34,217
Me? Why would you worry about me?

295
00:16:35,050 --> 00:16:38,050
The people you love most
are hurting right now.

296
00:16:38,350 --> 00:16:41,350
So naturally, you must be hurting too.

297
00:16:41,750 --> 00:16:42,750
What?

298
00:16:43,317 --> 00:16:45,550
They say people who understand
and empathize with others' pain...

299
00:16:45,550 --> 00:16:47,317
are overflowing with love.

300
00:16:49,417 --> 00:16:51,150
Well... Anyway,

301
00:16:51,650 --> 00:16:53,950
take good care of your mother.
See you tomorrow.

302
00:16:54,317 --> 00:16:55,417
Okay.

303
00:16:55,417 --> 00:16:57,050
Thank you for letting
my brother and Bit Na...

304
00:16:57,050 --> 00:16:59,017
stay together tonight, Team Manager.

305
00:17:01,017 --> 00:17:02,717
You said we're family, didn't you?

306
00:17:03,117 --> 00:17:05,117
Then why are you thanking me so formally?

307
00:17:06,117 --> 00:17:07,117
Get some sleep.

308
00:17:08,017 --> 00:17:11,517
Okay. See you at work tomorrow.
Good night.

309
00:17:16,317 --> 00:17:17,317
"Good night?"

310
00:17:20,917 --> 00:17:22,250
I'm pretty?

311
00:17:28,317 --> 00:17:31,417
Mr. Seo,
want to make it official starting today?

312
00:17:32,117 --> 00:17:33,117
What?

313
00:17:34,917 --> 00:17:36,317
Okay, deal.

314
00:17:37,350 --> 00:17:38,617
Stop it!

315
00:17:39,817 --> 00:17:43,150
How many times
are you going to repeat the same thing?

316
00:17:44,950 --> 00:17:47,650
Fine. Just date already.

317
00:17:47,917 --> 00:17:49,117
I'll be your witness.

318
00:17:49,117 --> 00:17:52,150
Wait. Who's dating who?

319
00:17:52,617 --> 00:17:54,917
Me and Oh Hye Ji?

320
00:17:56,317 --> 00:17:57,917
We're officially together starting today.

321
00:17:59,917 --> 00:18:01,217
Just now,

322
00:18:01,217 --> 00:18:04,150
you said you're officially together
starting today.

323
00:18:04,617 --> 00:18:06,450
What? I did?

324
00:18:07,250 --> 00:18:09,850
I don't usually hand out blessings
like this,

325
00:18:10,150 --> 00:18:11,317
so consider yourself lucky.

326
00:18:11,917 --> 00:18:15,217
Oh Hye Ji topped our medical school class.

327
00:18:15,217 --> 00:18:16,217
And she did that looking this good.

328
00:18:16,917 --> 00:18:20,617
Where are you going to find
a girlfriend this beautiful?

329
00:18:21,217 --> 00:18:22,417
Hold on.

330
00:18:23,150 --> 00:18:26,217
She's the prettiest in the class?

331
00:18:26,617 --> 00:18:27,617
Come on.

332
00:18:28,850 --> 00:18:30,650
The prettiest one...

333
00:18:32,550 --> 00:18:34,050
is Ms. Cho.

334
00:18:34,650 --> 00:18:36,117
What did you just say?

335
00:18:36,117 --> 00:18:37,150
You know...

336
00:18:38,150 --> 00:18:41,517
The one thing I absolutely can't do...

337
00:18:41,517 --> 00:18:43,717
is lie.

338
00:18:44,117 --> 00:18:47,750
Because of this honest mouth of mine,

339
00:18:47,750 --> 00:18:50,117
I...

340
00:18:53,617 --> 00:18:56,317
How am I prettier than Hye Ji?

341
00:19:11,050 --> 00:19:12,117
You're still here?

342
00:19:13,417 --> 00:19:15,217
I was just about to leave.

343
00:19:15,817 --> 00:19:16,817
What's that?

344
00:19:16,917 --> 00:19:20,717
This? It's my companion fish.

345
00:19:20,717 --> 00:19:21,717
Companion fish?

346
00:19:22,650 --> 00:19:24,150
Yes. My companion fish.

347
00:19:28,017 --> 00:19:30,117
You're making fun of me, aren't you?
Calling me a goldfish?

348
00:19:30,417 --> 00:19:33,917
Now way.
How could I possibly do that to you?

349
00:19:35,717 --> 00:19:36,817
Anyway...

350
00:19:37,017 --> 00:19:39,950
You've forgotten all about that day,
right?

351
00:19:40,117 --> 00:19:42,450
That day? What about that day?

352
00:19:45,317 --> 00:19:46,317
I remember now.

353
00:19:47,117 --> 00:19:49,517
You skipped out on cleaning that day.

354
00:19:49,617 --> 00:19:51,017
Skipped out?

355
00:19:51,650 --> 00:19:52,650
Come on.

356
00:19:53,250 --> 00:19:56,517
Such a pretty mouth
should say pretty things.

357
00:19:57,050 --> 00:19:58,650
A pretty mouth?

358
00:19:58,850 --> 00:20:00,850
Well, about that day...

359
00:20:02,017 --> 00:20:03,317
I'm sorry.

360
00:20:03,517 --> 00:20:06,250
Instead,
I'll do the cleaning for a whole week.

361
00:20:11,917 --> 00:20:14,117
He's like Prince Charming.

362
00:20:15,750 --> 00:20:18,017
Did the prince fall off his horse
and die or something?

363
00:20:18,350 --> 00:20:20,017
Prince Charming, my foot.

364
00:20:21,517 --> 00:20:23,717
Though his proportions are pretty good.

365
00:20:24,650 --> 00:20:27,217
Nine heads tall, maybe?

366
00:20:28,150 --> 00:20:29,417
Nine heads?

367
00:20:29,850 --> 00:20:31,517
Did you just call me stupid?

368
00:20:31,650 --> 00:20:33,017
What? When did I do that?

369
00:20:33,250 --> 00:20:34,250
Aren't you leaving?

370
00:20:34,350 --> 00:20:35,517
I'm going!

371
00:20:40,150 --> 00:20:41,217
I'm leaving because you're so petty.

372
00:20:41,217 --> 00:20:42,217
Petty?

373
00:20:50,550 --> 00:20:51,550
Cute.

374
00:20:52,017 --> 00:20:53,017
I should name them.

375
00:21:00,217 --> 00:21:02,217
You're already leaving for work?
Why so early?

376
00:21:02,717 --> 00:21:04,550
Starting today,
I can't have breakfast with everyone.

377
00:21:04,850 --> 00:21:06,217
I enrolled in a morning English class.

378
00:21:07,217 --> 00:21:08,850
- Good morning, Dad.
- Morning.

379
00:21:09,450 --> 00:21:11,017
An English class all of a sudden?

380
00:21:11,417 --> 00:21:13,350
You practically got a perfect TOEIC score.

381
00:21:13,350 --> 00:21:16,117
That's different.
I'll head straight to work from class.

382
00:21:16,217 --> 00:21:17,317
See you later.

383
00:21:17,450 --> 00:21:18,517
Hey, Seo Seung Ri!

384
00:21:19,617 --> 00:21:20,650
Just let her be.

385
00:21:21,350 --> 00:21:24,250
Her mind's a mess, so she's keeping busy.

386
00:21:26,250 --> 00:21:29,217
I even asked Madam...

387
00:21:29,817 --> 00:21:31,417
to help persuade Gyeol with the Chairman.

388
00:21:32,117 --> 00:21:34,217
But I don't think that'll work either.

389
00:21:34,717 --> 00:21:36,117
What am I supposed to do?

390
00:21:36,317 --> 00:21:39,417
What? You asked them to persuade Gyeol?

391
00:21:40,417 --> 00:21:41,817
Does that even make sense?

392
00:21:42,517 --> 00:21:44,717
I was that desperate.

393
00:21:49,017 --> 00:21:50,017
Yes.

394
00:21:51,150 --> 00:21:52,350
When are you meeting them?

395
00:21:53,550 --> 00:21:54,550
Yes.

396
00:21:57,517 --> 00:21:59,117
Who is he meeting now?

397
00:22:01,517 --> 00:22:03,450
Did they find Madam's daughter
or something?

398
00:22:04,917 --> 00:22:06,617
(Kangsu Construction)

399
00:22:15,117 --> 00:22:16,217
Chief Ko. What brings you here?

400
00:22:16,717 --> 00:22:18,517
I have something to discuss with you,
Mr. Seo.

401
00:22:19,717 --> 00:22:20,717
With me?

402
00:22:22,817 --> 00:22:24,817
Should we go down to the café
in the lobby?

403
00:22:25,417 --> 00:22:28,050
No. I'll step out for a bit.

404
00:22:28,050 --> 00:22:29,117
Talk comfortably.

405
00:22:29,417 --> 00:22:31,317
- Thank you, Mr. Cho.
- Sure.

406
00:22:36,150 --> 00:22:37,150
What is it?

407
00:22:37,517 --> 00:22:40,150
You don't know Seung Ri
is preparing to study abroad, do you?

408
00:22:40,350 --> 00:22:41,717
What? Study abroad?

409
00:22:42,117 --> 00:22:43,317
Yesterday, I saw...

410
00:22:43,817 --> 00:22:46,317
an MBA application to a university
in New York on her laptop.

411
00:22:46,817 --> 00:22:50,150
I think she's preparing to follow Gyeol.

412
00:22:52,050 --> 00:22:54,950
Like you said,
I was going to propose once Seung Ri...

413
00:22:55,250 --> 00:22:58,250
opened her heart a little.
But I don't think I can wait anymore.

414
00:22:58,750 --> 00:23:01,317
So you're saying
you're going to propose right away?

415
00:23:01,617 --> 00:23:04,317
Yes. She said she'll leave
after the competition.

416
00:23:04,950 --> 00:23:08,217
If her admission gets confirmed
before then, it'll be too late.

417
00:23:08,517 --> 00:23:10,617
She's willing to study abroad
just to follow Gyeol.

418
00:23:11,750 --> 00:23:14,150
Do you really think
she'll accept your proposal?

419
00:23:14,517 --> 00:23:17,350
Then are you just going to stand by...

420
00:23:17,750 --> 00:23:19,117
and watch her follow Gyeol?

421
00:23:21,150 --> 00:23:23,017
What are you two talking about?

422
00:23:23,750 --> 00:23:26,217
Who's studying abroad and who's proposing?

423
00:23:26,417 --> 00:23:28,017
It's nothing. I'll explain everything.

424
00:23:28,417 --> 00:23:29,417
You, get out.

425
00:23:29,517 --> 00:23:31,150
- Father.
- Didn't you hear me?

426
00:23:37,950 --> 00:23:39,150
From what I can tell,

427
00:23:40,217 --> 00:23:43,417
Min Ho is talking
about proposing to Seung Ri,

428
00:23:43,417 --> 00:23:45,550
and you're supporting it.

429
00:23:47,817 --> 00:23:50,817
Seo Gwon Sik,
do you really think that makes any sense?

430
00:23:51,017 --> 00:23:53,417
If they get married,
you and I become in-laws.

431
00:23:53,917 --> 00:23:56,650
I have absolutely no desire
to become your in-law.

432
00:23:56,917 --> 00:23:58,917
And I wasn't supporting it.

433
00:24:00,317 --> 00:24:02,317
I felt sorry for those kids
and their tangled emotions.

434
00:24:02,317 --> 00:24:03,517
You feel sorry for them?

435
00:24:03,517 --> 00:24:05,950
Sure, I bet you do.

436
00:24:06,350 --> 00:24:08,350
If Seung Ri suddenly accepts Min Ho,

437
00:24:08,350 --> 00:24:10,517
your wish would come true too.

438
00:24:10,517 --> 00:24:11,717
Hey, Ko Dae Chi!

439
00:24:15,850 --> 00:24:18,917
Ko Dae Chi?
Did you just call me Ko Dae Chi?

440
00:24:20,417 --> 00:24:23,117
Looks like you're about to hit me.

441
00:24:24,117 --> 00:24:25,750
Go ahead.

442
00:24:25,950 --> 00:24:27,617
Hit me.

443
00:24:28,550 --> 00:24:30,117
Why can't you? Go on.

444
00:24:30,117 --> 00:24:33,017
What are you two doing? Enough!

445
00:24:38,117 --> 00:24:40,617
How long are you going to keep this up?

446
00:24:41,117 --> 00:24:42,417
Did you forget you're at work?

447
00:24:42,817 --> 00:24:44,417
Listen carefully, both of you.

448
00:24:45,617 --> 00:24:48,750
No matter how good or successful you are,
you're still beneath me.

449
00:24:49,517 --> 00:24:51,817
And if I feel like it,
I can crush both of you.

450
00:24:54,317 --> 00:24:55,417
That punk...

451
00:25:00,517 --> 00:25:01,517
Seong Jun.

452
00:25:03,017 --> 00:25:05,050
Sometimes,
I regret the choice I made that day.

453
00:25:06,750 --> 00:25:09,117
Did you really throw it away?

454
00:25:11,250 --> 00:25:13,717
What are you talking about?

455
00:25:17,417 --> 00:25:18,950
I shouldn't have left it to you.

456
00:25:23,117 --> 00:25:24,450
There are
more cultural activity programs...

457
00:25:24,817 --> 00:25:28,350
and date-course candidates
than I expected.

458
00:25:28,917 --> 00:25:30,550
Especially
for the cultural experience programs,

459
00:25:30,550 --> 00:25:32,417
since we want to apply them
to our retirement community,

460
00:25:32,417 --> 00:25:34,350
I think we should
try them ourselves first.

461
00:25:34,750 --> 00:25:37,050
Yes, I agree.

462
00:25:37,417 --> 00:25:40,117
For these senior date courses,

463
00:25:40,117 --> 00:25:42,417
we'll need information
not just on locations,

464
00:25:42,417 --> 00:25:45,217
but also recommended duration,
food, and activities.

465
00:25:45,350 --> 00:25:46,417
Experiencing them firsthand is essential.

466
00:25:46,717 --> 00:25:49,417
How about we scout the courses ourselves
before designing them?

467
00:25:50,217 --> 00:25:52,050
That sounds good.
Then for the site visits...

468
00:25:52,450 --> 00:25:54,750
Team Manager, you already have
enough important work inside the office,

469
00:25:54,750 --> 00:25:56,250
so Ms. Cho Eun Ae and I will go.

470
00:25:56,617 --> 00:25:58,317
What? The two of you?

471
00:26:00,550 --> 00:26:02,150
Yes. That's okay, right, Ms. Cho Eun Ae?

472
00:26:02,550 --> 00:26:03,550
Of course.

473
00:26:03,817 --> 00:26:05,750
Then, shall we start planning the routes?

474
00:26:06,017 --> 00:26:07,017
Wait a second.

475
00:26:07,850 --> 00:26:09,817
I'm not the kind of team manager
who dumps all the hard work on the team...

476
00:26:09,817 --> 00:26:11,817
and sits in the office.

477
00:26:12,150 --> 00:26:13,650
I'm a hands-on manager.

478
00:26:13,817 --> 00:26:16,217
Then you and I can go together...

479
00:26:16,417 --> 00:26:20,750
No. I have a special assignment for you.

480
00:26:21,250 --> 00:26:24,550
Please gather examples
of AI-integrated retirement communities,

481
00:26:24,917 --> 00:26:27,817
and also summarize
the current AI systems being used...

482
00:26:27,817 --> 00:26:29,850
in apartments and retirement communities.

483
00:26:31,417 --> 00:26:32,617
Understood.

484
00:26:33,717 --> 00:26:35,717
Then I guess we have no choice.

485
00:26:36,050 --> 00:26:37,917
Ms. Cho Eun Ae and I
will handle the site visits.

486
00:26:38,050 --> 00:26:40,717
Intern Cho, you can start fieldwork
early tomorrow morning, right?

487
00:26:41,717 --> 00:26:42,817
Sure.

488
00:26:43,750 --> 00:26:46,217
Then shall we begin
by organizing the programs we'll try?

489
00:26:46,517 --> 00:26:47,517
Yes.

490
00:26:48,317 --> 00:26:51,817
- I'll head to the archive room.
- Okay.

491
00:26:54,417 --> 00:26:57,017
Team Manager, don't tell me...

492
00:26:58,350 --> 00:27:00,317
Don't tell you what?

493
00:27:01,217 --> 00:27:02,450
Nothing.

494
00:27:13,250 --> 00:27:15,817
Chief Ko, aren't you going home?

495
00:27:25,517 --> 00:27:27,517
(Seo Seung Ri, will you marry me?)

496
00:27:27,517 --> 00:27:28,517
Looks like he's going to propose.

497
00:27:28,517 --> 00:27:29,750
What? Were those two dating?

498
00:27:40,750 --> 00:27:41,750
I love you, Seung Ri.

499
00:27:42,917 --> 00:27:44,617
(Seo Seung Ri, Ko Min Ho)

500
00:28:04,217 --> 00:28:06,817
(Our Happy Days)

501
00:28:07,217 --> 00:28:09,317
What were you thinking,
doing that in front of everyone?

502
00:28:09,317 --> 00:28:10,650
Because I had no other choice.

503
00:28:10,650 --> 00:28:13,050
If you're really planning to study abroad,
this was the only way I could stop you.

504
00:28:13,050 --> 00:28:15,650
- You're preparing to study in the U.S.?
- Mom.

505
00:28:15,650 --> 00:28:18,617
Is it true you're planning
to study abroad to follow Gyeol?

506
00:28:18,717 --> 00:28:21,417
Team Manager Ko and Ms. Cho Eun Ae
aren't at work yet?

507
00:28:21,417 --> 00:28:24,917
I haven't seen her for one day,
but it feels like it's been months.

508
00:28:24,917 --> 00:28:26,717
Does that mean you...

509
00:28:27,317 --> 00:28:28,817
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
